article_title: Examining Plummeting Obamacare Enrollment, Part I

article_metadata.description: The administration estimates that about half as many people will enroll in an Obamacare exchange plan as experts projected at the time the law passed Congress. It turns out that Obamacare plans are not attractive to the young, relatively healthy, and non-poor.
article_metadata.author: The Apothecary
